<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 125 
                    The Secretary of State to the
                        Political Adviser in Germany (
                        Murphy
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d125</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">125</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-05T10:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-05T10:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-05T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/7–545:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 125 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Political Adviser in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRD1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-05T11:00:00-04:00">July 5, 1945—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. I wish to invite you to be present at the forthcoming meeting of the three
                    Heads of Government.</p>
                <p>Following is the list of State Department personnel totalling thirty-six people
                    who make up my party: Secretary <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>;
                    Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName>; Assistant Secretary <persName corresp="#p_CWL1">Clayton</persName>, Assistant Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJC1">Dunn</persName>; <persName corresp="#p_CBV1">Ben
                        Cohen</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Donald Russell</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">Walter Brown</persName>, Special Assistants to
                    the Secretary; <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">H. F. Matthews</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BCE2">C. E. Bohlen</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_TLE1">Llewellyn Thompson</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_PEJ1">Edward
                        Page</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_CEG1">Emilio Collado</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_RJW1">James Riddleberger</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_DE2">Emile Despres</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_CCW1">Cavendish Cannon</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_AGE1">George
                        Allen</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_EBGVJ1">J. C. Vincent</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_DEH1">Eugene Dooman</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MPE1">Philip Mosely</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_YCW1">Charles Yost</persName>, Colonel <persName corresp="#p_WCJS1">John
                        Wise</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_RRB1">R. B. Reams</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_FW1">Wilder Foote</persName> and an administrative and
                    secretarial staff of twelve.</p>
                <p>I should appreciate it if you would take proper steps to make sure that
                    appropriate arrangements are made in Berlin for this group which is scheduled to
                    arrive July 13.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">J[oseph] C. G[rew]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
